                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="33695" author="cedrik_lime" created="Fri, 21 Mar 2008 03:35:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also affected by this issue is the new (2.0) Md4PasswordEncoder#encodePassword. Same problem, same fix!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Replace:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;md4.update(saltedPass.getBytes(), 0, saltedPass.length());&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;byte[] saltedPassBytes = saltedPass.getBytes(org.apache.commons.lang.CharEncoding.UTF_8);&lt;br/&gt;
md4.update(saltedPassBytes, 0, saltedPassBytes.length());&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="33826" author="balex" created="Mon, 24 Mar 2008 11:51:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changed to RC1 given it&apos;s a simple change/fix, plus could affect backward compatibility so we should include in 2.0.0 so people review it as part of their upgrade.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="34104" author="luke" created="Sun, 30 Mar 2008 20:52:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve changed MessageDigestPasswordEncoder, LdapShaPasswordEncoder and Md4PasswordEncoder ro use UTF-8 when getting bytes from a String.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
